Friday August 30th 2013 12:55 pm -04:00,Marcio the 123 units example given in the Assignment handout regarding get_hours get_minues and get_seconds is very instructive in terms of the code you are being asked to write.Conceptually you have a certain number of seconds since midnight and you are being asked to first find the whole number of hours in that number of seconds (get_hours).  Unless the number is a multiple of 3600 (3600 seconds in an hour given by 60 minutes * 60 seconds) you will have a number of seconds remaining.  You are then being asked to find the whole number of minutes in those remaining seconds (get_minutes).  And finally you are being asked to find the number of seconds remaining having accounted for the whole hours and minutes (get_seconds)., Resolved,0
